-- Don't touch the spacing in the file.
-- It contains various invisible format effectors.

-- Refer to the Ada83 LRM sections 2.2 and 2.8

-- An average Ada83 comment - ending in a newline.

-- More than one comment -- On a line is still only one comment.


	  -- Comments don't have to start at the beginning of the line.
	  --The only thing is that they start with "--"

-- They can also contain 	tabs.
-- Or any character other than line ending format effectors for that matter.
-- ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ
-- abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz
-- 0123456789
-- " # & ' ( ) * + , - . / : ; < = > _ | 
-- ! $ % ? @ [ \ ] ^ ` { } ~

-- Comments can be empty
--


-- Comments are terminated by any of the following characters:
-- newline
-- return-- vertical tab----line feed--and the end of file